 ('1', '1', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-04-29 02:37:21', '2017-04-29 02:41:04', 'fb6de402-628f-40b6-b4b7-fcc570b4bbe2'),
 ('2', '2', 'en_us', 'Welcome to Blackfez.com!', '<p>It’s true, this site doesn’t have a whole lot of content yet, but don’t worry. Our web developers have just installed the CMS, and they’re setting things up for the content editors this very moment. Soon Blackfez.com will be an oasis of fresh perspectives, sharp analyses, and astute opinions that will keep you coming back again and again.</p>', NULL, '2017-04-29 02:37:23', '2017-04-29 02:37:23', '056b477d-1ad1-489c-bc3b-789bc8a41a0c'),
 ('4', '4', 'en_us', 'Frameworks', NULL, NULL, '2017-04-30 22:05:32', '2017-04-30 22:05:32', 'b0cd6b90-865e-4b82-9dbb-d211631e2cc4'),
 ('5', '5', 'en_us', 'CMS', NULL, NULL, '2017-04-30 22:05:39', '2017-04-30 22:05:39', '400ec3ce-994c-4c9b-9818-ea3e2857ab21'),
 ('6', '6', 'en_us', 'Craft CMS', '<p>My new favorite <abbr title=\"Content Management System\">CMS</abbr>.  The melding of control and flexibility is intoxicating.</p>', 'https://craftcms.com', '2017-04-30 22:05:47', '2017-04-30 22:05:47', '2bef6fb3-2d97-47dd-bbad-32cfb9268846'),
 ('7', '7', 'en_us', 'Craft', NULL, NULL, '2017-04-30 22:33:55', '2017-04-30 22:33:55', '89a904d3-b478-4072-b459-4ef9dd7a7242'),
 ('8', '8', 'en_us', 'Doing it!', '<p>Starting to build out some sample content for the new and improved Craft-based Nix Quips.  A joy and a half.</p>', NULL, '2017-04-30 22:34:02', '2017-04-30 22:34:02', 'fddb6c74-fe82-4524-9238-dfeee1e0e2a2'),
 ('9', '9', 'en_us', 'My new favorite thing', '<p>Craft CMS is my new favorite thing.  Well, as much as something written in PHP can qualify anyway.  But, seriously, the UI is slick and the flexibility supports any data model I want to throw at it.  Best of all, the HTML is exactly as clean and sparse as I make it.  </p><p>Sure, we\'re still in the salad days, but I got further with Craft in six hours than I ever did in the several weeks I played with Drupal.</p>', NULL, '2017-04-30 22:35:50', '2017-04-30 22:35:50', '3c1dbb57-dce3-4a36-bbcd-85d3abd85607'),
 ('10', '10', 'en_us', 'Matilda', NULL, NULL, '2017-04-30 22:44:41', '2017-04-30 22:44:41', '2eeee30b-9d61-442c-b8d8-a1f4cd965350'),
 ('11', '11', 'en_us', 'Repairs', NULL, NULL, '2017-04-30 22:46:35', '2017-04-30 22:46:53', 'cfc1e28b-8490-479c-953e-fe884949b9f2'),
 ('12', '12', 'en_us', 'Root cause', '<p>I think we\'re finally at root cause for the front wheel bearings issue that has plagued Matilda.  Previous owner did a lousy job of swapping in a custom wheel and it didn\'t fit well on the hub without some spacers.  The spacers were fiddly at best and when they shifted the out-of-true-ness made quick work of the bearings.  Dillon Bros is going to eat the replacement cost of an OEM Sportster front wheel as well as the bearings.  </p>\n<h3>The Good: </h3>\n<ul><li>It\'s always good to find root cause</li><li>Fixed at no cost to me</li><li>New wheel, presumably without the warp in the rim</li><li>I\'m not completely pissed with the dealer</li></ul><h3>The Bad:</h3>\n<ul><li>They sold a bike with a bum wheel</li><li>They replaced the bearings and put the bum wheel with the fiddly spacers on the bike last July without mentioning the issue</li><li>They replaced the tire a few weeks ago which involves re-mounting the front wheel and again didn\'t mention an issue with a custom wheel with fiddly spacers</li><li>The previous three points don\'t instill much confidence in the dealer\'s repair shop.</li><li>I\'m bike-free until late next week.  2+ weeks of no riding :\'(</li></ul>', NULL, '2017-04-30 22:49:51', '2017-04-30 22:50:34', '18d1e919-c692-4a94-878c-8b84b99fa48f'),
 ('13', '13', 'en_us', 'Game', NULL, NULL, '2017-04-30 22:52:22', '2017-04-30 22:52:22', '5430ee51-e82c-430b-821f-42a8df69abd9'),
